    "creation_date" : 1344867772,
    "answer_id" : 11936284,
    "question_id" : 11936220,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Hmm, I think it's related to XA. It works fine when I bracket the stored procedure with <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/cd/B14117_01/appdev.101/b10807/13_elems002.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION Pragma</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>PROCEDURE foo (val IN VARCHAR2(4000)) is\n  PRAGMA AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION;\n  BEGIN\n  INSERT INTO tbl1 VALUES (val);\n  DELETE FROM tbl2;\n  COMMIT;\nEND foo;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 41625,
      "reputation" : 6030,
      "user_id" : 121035,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4fd9eafda960d5054d63ad2c2cf9ecf9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "steve",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/121035/steve"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1344920297,
    "creation_date" : 1344920297,
    "answer_id" : 11946009,
    "question_id" : 11936220,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>What does the oracle documentation say about the error:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>COMMIT was issued in a session that is not the two-phase commit global\n  coordinator.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Basically you are executing a distributed transaction. As part of a distributed transaction you are trying to invoke an autonomous transaction. This is not possible as distributed transactions are required to do a 2PC.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 6326193,
        "reputation" : 6027,
        "user_id" : 4912604,
        "user_type" : "registered",
