      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "changing datasource from XA to connection pool worked for me"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1250235,
      "reputation" : 6748,
      "user_id" : 1210779,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 65,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/YAjnk.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sai Ye Yan Naing Aye",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1210779/sai-ye-yan-naing-aye"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1344920819,
    "creation_date" : 1344920819,
    "answer_id" : 11946069,
    "question_id" : 11936220,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Try this ways;</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Change the data source to use Non-XA (and check  the “Supports Global\nTransactions” &amp; “Emulate Two-Phase Commit” buttons)</li>\n<li>Delete the COMMIT from your code.</li>\n<li>Use the “PRAGMA AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION“. This will kind of create a\nseparate transaction that will allow to use a commit.For\nexample:CREATE PROCEDURE XXX AS PRAGMA AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION; BEGIN\n…</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7361132,
      "reputation" : 836,
      "user_id" : 6579203,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/l60et.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "xtermi2",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6579203/xtermi2"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1760614425,
    "creation_date" : 1760614425,
    "answer_id" : 79792091,
    "question_id" : 11936220,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>We had the same error. You also have to look for statements in your stored procedures which implicit do a commit like</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>TRUNCATE TABLE</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>We replaced it with a ordinary <code>DELETE FROM</code>, which fixed the error.</p>\n"
  } ],
